    {
      "id": "il43vqgnoXqTi21zSEce7",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 718.7758800983429,
      "y": 26.749613523483305,
      "width": 906.402587890625,
      "height": 520,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "a2",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 2078489097,
      "version": 783,
      "versionNonce": 1308632039,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1773397630280,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "n = number of words in words\nm = average length of a word\nk = total number of common letters\n\n\nfor letter in words[0]:                            iterates over all letters of the first word  => O(m)\n    array_g[ord(letter) - ord('a')] += 1           increment on an array                        => O(1)\n\n\n\ntempo = [0]*26           → O(26)      => O(1) \nfor letter in word       → O(m)\nfor i in range(26)       → O(26)      => O(1) constant\n\n\nSo : O(m + 26 + 26) => O(m) (since 26 is constant)\n\nThere are n-1 words, so total: O((n-1)m) => O(nm)\n\nfor i in range(26):                                      → O(26)   => O(1)\n    result.extend([chr(i + ord('a'))] * array_g[i])\n\nTotal: O(k) (k ≤ n*m)\n                    \n                \n                    O(m) + O(nm) + O(k) => O(nm)",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "n = number of words in words\nm = average length of a word\nk = total number of common letters\n\n\nfor letter in words[0]:                            iterates over all letters of the first word  => O(m)\n    array_g[ord(letter) - ord('a')] += 1           increment on an array                        => O(1)\n\n\n\ntempo = [0]*26           → O(26)      => O(1) \nfor letter in word       → O(m)\nfor i in range(26)       → O(26)      => O(1) constant\n\n\nSo : O(m + 26 + 26) => O(m) (since 26 is constant)\n\nThere are n-1 words, so total: O((n-1)m) => O(nm)\n\nfor i in range(26):                                      → O(26)   => O(1)\n    result.extend([chr(i + ord('a'))] * array_g[i])\n\nTotal: O(k) (k ≤ n*m)\n                    \n                \n                    O(m) + O(nm) + O(k) => O(nm)",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "cTYGdDm8CgrT7V66RI_tK",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 118.70299768447876,
      "y": 455.112042427063,
      "width": 545.6011352539062,
      "height": 240,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "a9",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1869858471,
      "version": 1197,
      "versionNonce": 1427669351,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773397661968,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "What takes up memory:\n\n    - array_g = [0]*26 → O(26) = O(1) constant\n\n    - tempo = [0]*26 → O(26) = O(1) constant per word\n\n    - result = contains all the common letters \n             => O(k) where k ≤ sum of the lengths of the words\n\n            \n                    O(1) + O(1) + O(k) = O(k)\n        ",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "What takes up memory:\n\n    - array_g = [0]*26 → O(26) = O(1) constant\n\n    - tempo = [0]*26 → O(26) = O(1) constant per word\n\n    - result = contains all the common letters \n             => O(k) where k ≤ sum of the lengths of the words\n\n            \n                    O(1) + O(1) + O(k) = O(k)\n        ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
